---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout title="Now" description="What Kyle Daley is doing now — current focus, reading, and projects.">
  <header class="mb-10">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 mb-2">
      Now
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400">
      A snapshot of what I'm doing — updated irregularly.
      <a href="https://nownownow.com/about" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand-600 dark:text-brand-300 hover:underline ml-1">What is a now page?</a>
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert max-w-none prose-a:text-brand-600 dark:prose-a:text-brand-300">
    <h2>Work</h2>
    <p>
      Professionally, most of my time right now is going into Azure workload
      migrations: moving Cloud Services (extended support) to Azure App
      Services + VM Scale Sets, migrating AKS workloads to Azure Container
      Apps, and consolidating a sprawl of Azure directories and subscriptions
      into something saner. In between, I'm updating our CI/CD pipelines to
      keep pace with all of it.
    </p>

    <h2>Learning</h2>
    <p>
      Brushing the dust off TypeScript and picking up Python and FastAPI.
      Different ecosystem, similar itch. I like poking at a new stack every
      so often just to see how someone else solved the same problems I've
      been solving in .NET for twenty years.
    </p>

    <h2>Building</h2>
    <p>
      This site, mostly. It's my main personal project at the moment, equal
      parts notebook, résumé, and excuse to keep tinkering with Astro and
      React. I'm also gearing up for a new program year with our{' '}
      <a href="https://tx0521.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Trail Life troop, TX-0521</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Reading</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Acts (the Bible)</li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/1433592533" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">On the Christian Life: A New Translation</a>{' '}
        by John Calvin
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Thinking about</h2>
    <p>
      We've had a lot of change lately. It's been good change, but still new,
      and I've been chewing on what God is trying to teach me through it.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p class="mt-12 text-xs text-neutral-400 dark:text-neutral-500">
    Last updated: July 2026
  </p>
</PageLayout>
